# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code uses a common JavaScript obfuscation pattern with:
1. A **string array** (`a0_0x4453`) containing base64-encoded strings
2. A **decoder function** (`a0_0x305b`) that retrieves and decodes strings by index
3. A **shuffling IIFE** that rotates the string array until a checksum matches
4. Hex number literals and mangled variable names

## Fully Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // ~√(1/2)

// Physics configuration
const config = {
  repulsionStrength: 4000,
  frictionCoeff: 0.004,
  amplitudeDamping: 0.92,
  dispersal: 0.0003,
  streamMax: 40,
  viscosity: 0.04,
  lerp: 0.06
};

// ===== NODES (graph vertices) =====
const nodes = [
  { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ===== EDGES (spring connections) =====
const edges = [
  { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera / viewport state
let camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle stream
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// ===== PHYSICS SIMULATION =====
function simulate() {
  // 1) Node-node REPULSION (Coulomb-like)
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      let force = config.repulsionStrength / (dist * dist);
      let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      let fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2) Edge SPRING ATTRACTION (Hooke's law)
  for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
    let nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
    let nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
    let dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    let dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    let displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
    let force = (edges[i].k || config.frictionCoeff) * displacement;
    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3) CENTERING force + velocity DAMPING + position integration
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.dispersal;
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.dispersal;
    nodes[i].vx *= config.amplitudeDamping;
    nodes[i].vy *= config.amplitudeDamping;
    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}

// ===== PARTICLE EMITTER =====
function emitParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.streamMax) return;
  let sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  let angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;
  particles.push({
    x: sourceNode.x,
    y: sourceNode.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2
  });
}

// ===== PARTICLE UPDATE =====
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    let p = particles[i];
    p.vx *= 1 - config.viscosity * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.viscosity * 0.125;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}

// ===== CAMERA SMOOTHING =====
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.lerp;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.lerp;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.lerp;
}

// ===== MAIN LOOP =====
function tick() {
  simulate();         // physics
  frameCount++;
  updateParticles();  // move & cull particles
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) emitParticle(); // spawn every 3rd frame
  updateCamera();     // smooth camera
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout engine** with decorative particles — the kind of thing you'd see in a network visualization or interactive node diagram.

### Core Systems:

| System | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Repulsion** | Nodes push each other apart (inverse-square law, like electric charges) |
| **Spring Attraction** | Connected nodes are pulled together (Hooke's law with rest lengths) |
| **Centering Gravity** | Weak force pulling everything toward center (400, 300) |
| **Velocity Damping** | 0.92 multiplier each frame prevents runaway oscillation |
| **Particle Stream** | Cosmetic particles emitted from random nodes, drifting outward and fading with age |
| **Camera Lerp** | Smooth interpolation toward a target camera position/zoom |

### The Graph Structure:
```
        Epsilon
          |
  Gamma--Hub--Alpha
          |      |
        Delta  Beta
          |      |
        (gamma--delta, alpha--beta cross-links)
```

A **central "Hub" node** connects to 5 satellite nodes, with a few cross-connections. The hub is the largest (r=26), satellites are smaller (r=12–16). The simulation runs at **~60 FPS** via `setInterval(..., 16)` but notably has **no rendering code** — this is purely the simulation/data layer, likely paired with a separate Canvas/SVG renderer not shown here.
